featured_question.question:
(Translated by Google) Who built the new mosque?

(Original)
BAdi masjid kisne banvaya
featured_question.answer:
(Translated by Google) Located 2.2 km north-east of Jaunpur, Jama Masjid is also known as Badi Masjid, Juma Masjid and Jami Masjid. It was built by Hussain Shah Sharqi in the 15th century around 1470 AD. Its architectural design is very similar to the Atala Masjid of Jaunpur and the Mughal monuments of Delhi. This mosque is built on a six meter high foundation. To reach inside, there is a huge door, above which there are two arches.
The main prayer hall of the mosque is a nave, covered with a dome. The diameter of this huge dome is 11.4 meters. There are small windows in the mosque to allow sunlight to enter. The inside and outside walls of the mosque are decorated with typical Mughal style artworks.
 Beams or lintels have been used in the arches built in this mosque in Tughlaq style. The structure of the gallery surrounded by lattices in the mosque is an important feature of Jaunpur style. The graves of Hussain Shah and his family members are situated in the courtyard adjacent to the mosque. According to the local people, this cemetery is very surprising.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Huge Mosque is in Jaunpur.
It was built by Hussein Shah Shirki in 15th century around 1470 ad.
It is about 2.5 km away from kotwali chauraha.its architectural style is same as other monument in Delhi.
Big door to get inside the mosjid and big ground where muslim's prayer.
There are graves of hussein and his family member in the menstion situated in the mosque.
Outer wall was made by red stone in mughal style and there was a small pond situated in middle of the mosque where muslim use water to clean his hand and leg for prayer.
The architecture of the mosque is beautiful and small windows designed for sunlight and air.
